Hi Alyssa,<br><br>Sure, please see below:<br><h3>✅ Step 1: Add Custom JavaScript to Each Form (We can do STEP 1)</h3>In Elementor, for <strong>each form</strong>, do the following:<br><ol><li>Go to the form’s settings.<br></li><li>Under <strong>"Actions After Submit"</strong>, add <strong>"JavaScript"</strong>.<br></li><li>In the JavaScript field, insert this snippet (update the <code class="inline-code">formName</code>  to something unique per form):<br></li></ol><pre><code class="inline-code">document.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent("elementor_form_submitted", {
  detail: {
    formId: '{{ID}}',
    formName: 'Contact Form',         // Change this label per form
    pageURL: window.location.href     // Optional, tracks the page location
  }
}));</code>
</pre>Repeat this for each form you'd like to track, updating the <code class="inline-code">formName</code>  value accordingly.<br><br><h3>✅ Step 2: Create a Custom Event Trigger in GTM</h3><ol><li>In GTM, go to <strong>Triggers &gt; New</strong>.<br></li><li>Set trigger type as <strong>Custom Event</strong>.<br></li><li>Event Name: <code class="inline-code">elementor_form_submitted</code> .<br></li><li>Trigger on <strong>All Custom Events</strong> (or filter by form ID later if needed).<br></li></ol><br><h3>✅ Step 3: Create Data Layer Variables</h3>Create the following variables in GTM to extract form data:<br><ul><li><code class="inline-code">event_detail_formId</code>  → Data Layer Variable: <code class="inline-code">event.detail.formId</code> <br></li><li><code class="inline-code">event_detail_formName</code>  → Data Layer Variable: <code class="inline-code">event.detail.formName</code> <br></li><li><code class="inline-code">event_detail_pageURL</code>  → Data Layer Variable: <code class="inline-code">event.detail.pageURL</code>  <em>(optional)</em><br></li></ul><br><h3>✅ Step 4: Set Up GA4 Event Tag in GTM</h3><ol><li>Go to <strong>Tags &gt; New</strong> and create a <strong>GA4 Event Tag</strong>.<br></li><li>Select your existing GA4 Configuration Tag.<br></li><li>Set <strong>Event Name</strong> to: <code class="inline-code">form_submission</code> .<br>Add Event Parameters:<br><ul><li><code class="inline-code">form_id</code>  → <code class="inline-code">{{event_detail_formId}}</code> <br></li><li><code class="inline-code">form_name</code>  → <code class="inline-code">{{event_detail_formName}}</code> <br></li><li><code class="inline-code">page_url</code>  → <code class="inline-code">{{event_detail_pageURL}}</code>  <em>(optional)</em><br></li></ul></li></ol>Attach the <strong>Custom Event Trigger</strong> you created earlier.<br><br><h3>✅ Step 5: Test the Setup</h3><ul><li>Use GTM’s <strong>Preview Mode</strong> to test form submissions.<br>Submit each Elementor form and verify:<br><ul><li>The correct event is triggered in GTM.<br></li><li>Parameters such as <code class="inline-code">form_name</code>  populate properly.<br></li></ul></li><li>Use <strong>GA4 DebugView</strong> or <strong>Realtime reports</strong> to confirm events are received.<br></li></ul>
